WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:04.870
Windmill Village,
East Blue

3
00:03:05.250 --> 00:03:06.210
Garp?!

4
00:03:06.210 --> 00:03:08.460
He disappeared at the Pirate Island?!

5
00:03:08.460 --> 00:03:09.880
Is that true?!

6
00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:13.380
He went there to go rescue
this Koby guy, didn't he?

7
00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:16.260
He must've sacrificed himself for his friend...

8
00:03:16.260 --> 00:03:18.140
It doesn't say he's dead!

9
00:03:18.510 --> 00:03:21.510
He's a man with many legends to his name!

10
00:03:21.510 --> 00:03:23.220
Don't worry yourselves.

11
00:03:23.220 --> 00:03:25.270
Very true, Mayor.

12
00:03:25.270 --> 00:03:26.770
Obviously.

13
00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:31.480
Who's laughing?! What's so funny?!

14
00:03:34.860 --> 00:03:35.950
Oh, goodness.

15
00:03:36.570 --> 00:03:38.450
That scared you, huh?

16
00:03:38.450 --> 00:03:39.570
There, there...

17
00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:41.330
Oh, it's just you...

18
00:03:41.330 --> 00:03:42.540
I'm sorry, Makino.

19
00:03:43.290 --> 00:03:46.160
I know you're worried about Garp.

20
00:03:46.160 --> 00:03:49.580
Recently, this little one has started
to recognize Luffy's face.

21
00:03:47.370 --> 00:03:49.580
"Straw Hats' Hostage Situation"

22
00:03:50.170 --> 00:03:52.960
You love your big bro Luffy, don't you?

23
00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:58.010
Freakin' Garp and Luffy...

24
00:03:58.010 --> 00:03:59.590
What are you doing?!

25
00:04:03.310 --> 00:04:07.600
Hostage Situation

26
00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:17.860
It's a big one!

27
00:04:22.370 --> 00:04:24.330
East Blue

28
00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:24.330
It's an earthquake!

29
00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:28.750
Daddy!

30
00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:34.210
South Blue

31
00:04:33.170 --> 00:04:35.550
There's a tsunami on the way!

32
00:04:35.550 --> 00:04:37.130
Get to high ground!

33
00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:39.130
West Blue

34
00:04:38.130 --> 00:04:40.090
Over here! Please hurry!

35
00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:44.640
North Blue

36
00:04:45.310 --> 00:04:46.350
This one's huge!

37
00:04:47.890 --> 00:04:56.980
The earthquake on that day
was unprecedented in recorded history.


It left severe damage
in its wake across the world.

38
00:04:48.890 --> 00:04:52.520
The earthquake on that day
was unprecedented in recorded history.

39
00:04:52.520 --> 00:04:56.980
It left severe damage
in its wake across the world.

40
00:04:57.990 --> 00:04:59.950
Grand Line

41
00:05:06.870 --> 00:05:09.660
Run! Get to higher ground!

42
00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:11.290
We're too late...

43
00:05:17.630 --> 00:05:22.050
Its epicenter could not be detected,
making it a seismological anomaly.

44
00:05:22.430 --> 00:05:24.470
Though the connection is unclear...

45
00:05:24.890 --> 00:05:28.850
it happened six days after the Kingdom
of Lulusia was wiped off the map...

46
00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:31.350
without anyone knowing about it.

47
00:05:31.350 --> 00:05:33.860
I'm here at the the former site of Lulusia!

48
00:05:34.480 --> 00:05:36.320
There's no trace of land anymore!

49
00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:38.900
Only a giant hole with water pouring into it!

50
00:05:39.240 --> 00:05:41.070
No further approach is possible!

51
00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:42.860
The hole shows no signs of filling!

52
00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:51.080
The earthquake caused sea levels around
the world to rise by approximately one meter.

53
00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:56.340
Vayyt! Vhaat is happening?!

54
00:06:00.970 --> 00:06:03.970
The beach has never flooded like this!

55
00:06:03.970 --> 00:06:05.850
The tide vill ebb eventually, right?!

56
00:06:05.850 --> 00:06:07.310
I can't take it!

57
00:06:08.060 --> 00:06:11.560
I wanted to run on the beach!

58
00:06:12.350 --> 00:06:14.190
Come on!

59
00:06:14.190 --> 00:06:17.060
Give us back our beach!

60
00:06:18.320 --> 00:06:21.530
A number of beaches around
the world have disappeared,

61
00:06:21.530 --> 00:06:24.030
along with several islands.

62
00:06:26.570 --> 00:06:28.700
We lost our home to the flood!

63
00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:31.660
A shark swam right into my house!

64
00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:35.830
It's not supposed to be high tide yet!

65
00:06:35.830 --> 00:06:37.840
Maybe today's catch will be huge.

66
00:06:37.840 --> 00:06:40.090
No, idiot! Don't sail out in this!

67
00:06:42.840 --> 00:06:45.380
Update regarding the global flooding...

68
00:06:46.510 --> 00:06:48.890
Sea levels are rising around the world?!

69
00:06:49.430 --> 00:06:50.430
Yes, sir.

70
00:06:50.430 --> 00:06:52.310
I don't understand what's happening...

71
00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:56.900
Meanwhile, in the New World...
Future Island, Egghead...

72
00:06:56.900 --> 00:07:01.360
was surrounded by a fleet
of one hundred ships

73
00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:03.820
—including twenty massive battleships—

74
00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:07.870
that far outclassed the nation-sized fleet
a buster call could summon.

75
00:07:08.490 --> 00:07:11.370
Aboard those ships were 30,000 Marines.

76
00:07:12.620 --> 00:07:15.210
Leading this unprecedented military force...

77
00:07:21.090 --> 00:07:24.010
were nine vice admirals
from Marine Headquarters...

78
00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:31.260
and...

79
00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:34.480
Admiral Kizaru.

80
00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:38.440
Here they come!

81
00:08:14.470 --> 00:08:15.100
Hey!

82
00:08:15.980 --> 00:08:19.560
Didn't I tell you not to attack
the weaponized sea beasts?!

83
00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:23.770
Well, it attacked us first.

84
00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:26.740
Kizaru, sir, your meal.

85
00:08:28.110 --> 00:08:30.530
Oh, looks good!

86
00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:31.990
All yours!

87
00:08:31.990 --> 00:08:33.660
Chopsticks are over there!

88
00:08:40.670 --> 00:08:45.210
Gotta say, I'm not sure I'm
comfortable with this, Sentomaru.

89
00:08:46.130 --> 00:08:49.880
Why not surrender and come back to us?

90
00:08:49.880 --> 00:08:53.220
You try that again, and we return fire, Unc!

91
00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:55.720
That's real scary.

92
00:08:55.720 --> 00:09:02.100
Old Man Punk developed the pacifista's
lasers by studying your abilities, y'know.

93
00:09:02.100 --> 00:09:04.270
Whoa, awesome!

94
00:09:05.610 --> 00:09:09.360
I never thought you'd come to
get rid of Old Man Punk...

95
00:09:09.740 --> 00:09:16.240
Studying the Void Century is a crime
even I can't defend, Sentomaru.

96
00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:17.580
I'm just...

97
00:09:18.040 --> 00:09:19.960
a cog in the machine.

98
00:09:21.420 --> 00:09:25.920
It's not like we stand to gain anything
from this battle, either.

99
00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:28.920
The more we destroy, the more we lose.

100
00:09:28.920 --> 00:09:33.260
Seems Rob Lucci's agents
couldn't get the job done.

101
00:09:33.260 --> 00:09:35.680
Yeah, thanks to the Straw Hats.

102
00:09:35.720 --> 00:09:39.640
On a Battleship...

103
00:09:40.810 --> 00:09:43.650
Do not let them know that I am here.

104
00:09:43.650 --> 00:09:44.610
Yes, sir.

105
00:09:45.060 --> 00:09:50.070
"The Straw Hat Pirates took Vegapunk hostage
and barricaded themselves on the island," huh?

106
00:09:50.070 --> 00:09:51.740
Not a bad piece.

107
00:09:52.320 --> 00:09:53.700
That would be Morgans'.

108
00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:55.530
And what of the truth?

109
00:09:56.030 --> 00:09:59.500
Sir! We have received no word that
CP0 has completed their mission.

110
00:10:00.540 --> 00:10:03.460
Given that Sentomaru
is still defending the island...

111
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:06.420
we know that the people in the Labophase are:

112
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:10.340
the main Dr. Vegapunk and his six satellites,

113
00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:14.140
the four seraphim protecting him,

114
00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:19.390
and the ten members of Emperor
Straw Hat's crew, believed to be allied with them.

115
00:10:22.350 --> 00:10:28.770
The commanders of CP0's lead unit,
Rob Lucci, Kaku, and Stussy...

116
00:10:28.770 --> 00:10:33.740
seem to have been captured alongside
other Cipher Pol agents by Sentomaru...

117
00:10:33.740 --> 00:10:36.660
and his pacifista Mk. III units
in the Fabriophase.

118
00:10:37.530 --> 00:10:42.790
The Frontier Dome's
barrier status is at 100 percent,

119
00:10:42.790 --> 00:10:46.250
so entering or exiting
the Labophase is impossible.

120
00:10:46.250 --> 00:10:52.300
It's been a full day, yet we still
have no intel on what's happening inside.

121
00:10:52.920 --> 00:10:57.850
Where have the research staff
and technicians who work on Egghead gone?

122
00:10:58.220 --> 00:11:01.270
As of yesterday, they've all evacuated.

123
00:11:01.640 --> 00:11:03.560
We've already located their ships.

124
00:11:03.560 --> 00:11:06.230
What if they know too much?

125
00:11:06.980 --> 00:11:08.690
Sink them immediately.

126
00:11:08.690 --> 00:11:09.440
Yes, sir!

127
00:11:10.480 --> 00:11:12.610
St. Saturn, one more thing!

128
00:11:12.610 --> 00:11:16.740
Jewelry Bonney the Glutton
has also been sighted on the island!

129
00:11:16.740 --> 00:11:18.450
Kuma's daughter, eh?

130
00:11:18.990 --> 00:11:20.830
We have no further use for her.

131
00:11:22.790 --> 00:11:25.620
Forget her. She is a mere girl.

132
00:11:25.620 --> 00:11:26.290
Understood.

133
00:11:29.130 --> 00:11:29.960
Kizaru, sir!

134
00:11:33.630 --> 00:11:36.130
I'm in the middle of eating...

135
00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:38.390
We're picking up a signal from Egghead!

136
00:11:39.760 --> 00:11:41.760
Seems they're calling somewhere!

137
00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:44.230
Just find out who they're calling, quickly.

138
00:11:48.690 --> 00:11:49.610
It's Mary Geoise!

139
00:11:49.650 --> 00:11:51.980
Mary Geoise
The Holy Land

140
00:11:55.320 --> 00:11:56.650
Who is this?

141
00:11:57.240 --> 00:12:01.030
Admiral, that thing on your wrist
is a black wiretapper snail.

142
00:12:02.280 --> 00:12:04.040
You can tap the call.

143
00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:15.420
Hello?! It's me!

144
00:12:15.420 --> 00:12:16.920
York!

145
00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:18.050
Oh, it's you.

146
00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:19.760
What are you doing?!

147
00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:21.010
What's your problem?!

148
00:12:21.010 --> 00:12:24.100
Why are you trying to kill me, too?!

149
00:12:22.140 --> 00:12:27.270
Room of Authority

150
00:12:24.100 --> 00:12:27.270
I gave you the intel about Stella's betrayal!

151
00:12:27.770 --> 00:12:32.020
You are also a Vegapunk, York.

152
00:12:32.360 --> 00:12:38.490
If I was interested in the Void Century,
there's no way I would've tattled on him!

153
00:12:38.860 --> 00:12:39.450
How disappointing!

154
00:12:39.450 --> 00:12:40.360
How disappointing!

155
00:12:41.910 --> 00:12:43.280
That is true.

156
00:12:43.280 --> 00:12:45.160
I am surprised you are alive.

157
00:12:45.160 --> 00:12:47.370
Did CP0 not come?

158
00:12:47.960 --> 00:12:50.790
What is the status of the Straw Hats?

159
00:12:52.750 --> 00:12:54.840
The fact that I'm the only one
talking to you after last night...

160
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:56.800
The fact that I'm the only one
talking to you after last night...

161
00:12:57.550 --> 00:13:00.180
should tell you everything!

162
00:13:02.510 --> 00:13:05.140
Egghead is all mine now!

163
00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:07.850
And...

164
00:13:08.930 --> 00:13:11.350
even if you try to harm me,

165
00:13:12.060 --> 00:13:13.310
I've got...

166
00:13:20.820 --> 00:13:22.280
the seraphim!

167
00:13:25.080 --> 00:13:25.740
So...

168
00:13:26.410 --> 00:13:29.200
what's with the fleet surrounding the island?

169
00:13:29.710 --> 00:13:32.000
You wanna go to war with me?

170
00:13:32.460 --> 00:13:35.630
York, we have had a change of heart.

171
00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:41.880
You are able to create this so-called
Mother Flame as well, are you not?

172
00:13:47.310 --> 00:13:49.480
Oh, so now you wanna play along?

173
00:13:49.480 --> 00:13:52.140
I knew you'd want it!

174
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:53.940
Glad I sent it to you.

175
00:13:54.730 --> 00:13:56.900
Yes, it is desired.

176
00:13:56.900 --> 00:13:58.480
Desired?

177
00:13:58.480 --> 00:13:59.860
By who?

178
00:13:59.860 --> 00:14:02.860
The power plant used to
make it is here on the island.

179
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.040
Listen up.

180
00:14:15.420 --> 00:14:19.380
Promise me you won't hurt me or the lab.

181
00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:20.800
We promise.

182
00:14:21.170 --> 00:14:23.550
And make me a Celestial Dragon!

183
00:14:23.550 --> 00:14:25.260
Consider it done.

184
00:14:25.760 --> 00:14:28.220
Then you've got a deal!

185
00:14:28.220 --> 00:14:30.430
So how about you guys...

186
00:14:31.680 --> 00:14:34.650
hurry up and save me already?!

187
00:14:34.650 --> 00:14:39.900
Straw Hat Luffy is gonna kill me!

188
00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:41.280
– What?!
– What?!

189
00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:42.150
What is this?!

190
00:14:42.150 --> 00:14:43.860
What's happening?

191
00:14:47.120 --> 00:14:48.660
Hey, Luffy!

192
00:14:48.660 --> 00:14:50.870
What do we do with her?

193
00:14:50.870 --> 00:14:52.620
She's no use to us anymore.

194
00:14:54.870 --> 00:14:59.590
Come crush these lunatics!

195
00:15:00.130 --> 00:15:02.760
That's what was happening, huh?

196
00:15:02.760 --> 00:15:04.840
Sorry for all the trouble we caused.

197
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:09.100
So that's how it is.
I'm starting to see the full picture.

198
00:15:09.100 --> 00:15:10.810
Luffy, what should we do with her?

199
00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:15.560
I dunno...

200
00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:17.940
Use her as a shield to escape or something?

201
00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:20.360
This is kinda like a hostage situation.

202
00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:23.280
How are Robin's injuries?

203
00:15:23.280 --> 00:15:27.240
They'll take some time to heal,
but she'll be fine as long as she rests.

204
00:15:29.950 --> 00:15:32.410
Hello?!

205
00:15:33.910 --> 00:15:34.620
My name is...

206
00:15:34.620 --> 00:15:35.370
My name is...

207
00:15:35.750 --> 00:15:37.750
Monkey D. Luffy!

208
00:15:37.750 --> 00:15:40.000
The man who's gonna be King of the Pirates!

209
00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:42.590
Wait, wait, Luffy! What are you saying?!

210
00:15:42.920 --> 00:15:46.300
We've got Dr. Vegapunk!

211
00:15:47.130 --> 00:15:49.260
If you value York's life,

212
00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:53.470
get all the Marine ships away from the shore!

213
00:15:53.470 --> 00:15:55.230
Help me!

214
00:15:55.230 --> 00:15:57.690
Straw Hat's gonna kill me!

215
00:15:59.310 --> 00:16:00.560
He's pure evil!

216
00:16:00.560 --> 00:16:03.280
He's as vicious as they say...

217
00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:05.860
World Economic News

218
00:16:04.280 --> 00:16:05.860
The hell is he doing?!

219
00:16:05.860 --> 00:16:08.240
What?! Luffy?!

220
00:16:08.240 --> 00:16:09.820
What's going on over there?!

221
00:16:10.410 --> 00:16:12.620
You would be Straw Hat Luffy?

222
00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:17.160
Who is still alive on Egghead?

223
00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.250
Well, let's see... We've got
some injured people, and...

224
00:16:21.960 --> 00:16:23.420
Luffy, no!

225
00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:28.470
A woman's voice...

226
00:16:28.880 --> 00:16:30.640
Nico Robin's, perhaps?

227
00:16:30.640 --> 00:16:32.760
What was that for?!

228
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:34.640
Information is a weapon.

229
00:16:34.640 --> 00:16:36.520
You must not hand it over so easily.

230
00:16:37.270 --> 00:16:38.600
Gotcha. Sorry.

231
00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:41.100
But now the ships are gonna be gone!

232
00:16:41.100 --> 00:16:42.310
Oh, like hell!

233
00:16:42.690 --> 00:16:44.980
You think the Marines are that dumb?!

234
00:16:46.990 --> 00:16:48.490
St. Saturn...

235
00:16:48.490 --> 00:16:50.700
There are three things we must protect.

236
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:52.950
York's safety.

237
00:16:52.950 --> 00:16:55.410
Their brain, Punk Records.

238
00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:59.040
The power plant that creates
the Mother Flame.

239
00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:01.460
All else is expendable.

240
00:17:03.460 --> 00:17:07.550
But Rob Lucci and the other
Cipher Pol agents are still inside of...

241
00:17:07.550 --> 00:17:09.880
I speak only of a worst-case scenario.

242
00:17:10.430 --> 00:17:13.220
Don't lose sight of our highest priorities.

243
00:17:14.510 --> 00:17:18.270
You'd do well to consider human lives
as nothing more than insects.

244
00:17:18.270 --> 00:17:20.890
Even with dwindling numbers,
they recover quickly.

245
00:17:26.360 --> 00:17:27.230
Yes, sir!

246
00:17:28.150 --> 00:17:30.530
All of you, listen here!

247
00:17:30.530 --> 00:17:33.660
Touch me and the Five Elders
will obliterate the island!

248
00:17:33.660 --> 00:17:36.910
They promised! Got that, morons?!

249
00:17:36.910 --> 00:17:38.790
It'll be another Ohara!

250
00:17:49.090 --> 00:17:50.670
Owie!

251
00:17:51.170 --> 00:17:52.550
You asked for it!

252
00:17:52.550 --> 00:17:54.550
I'm telling the Five Elders!

253
00:17:54.550 --> 00:17:56.760
Be my guest!

254
00:17:57.140 --> 00:18:00.600
You've got some nerve saying something
like that in front of Robin!

255
00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:03.480
You're the one asking for it here!

256
00:18:04.060 --> 00:18:06.190
Chill out. She's unarmed.

257
00:18:07.150 --> 00:18:09.780
Robin, are you feeling okay?

258
00:18:09.780 --> 00:18:13.280
Yes, thanks to you, Chopper.

259
00:18:14.030 --> 00:18:16.490
You're not making me happy, you dummy!

260
00:18:18.910 --> 00:18:20.250
This is the pits!

261
00:18:20.620 --> 00:18:24.580
But I was against two seraphim
at the same time.

262
00:18:26.960 --> 00:18:28.170
Just sleep.

263
00:18:30.300 --> 00:18:32.300
Shaka!

264
00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:34.300
Pythagoras!

265
00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:35.680
Edison!

266
00:18:35.680 --> 00:18:38.310
Edison's still alive, Lilith!

267
00:18:38.310 --> 00:18:39.890
Oh, thank goodness!

268
00:18:41.520 --> 00:18:43.640
Keep it down, Lilith.

269
00:18:43.640 --> 00:18:45.600
I'm trying to contact the basement.

270
00:18:49.070 --> 00:18:52.110
Hey, you guys behaving down there?

271
00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:54.320
Straw Hats!

272
00:18:55.320 --> 00:19:00.990
Basement, Labophase

273
00:18:55.740 --> 00:18:58.080
Thanks so much for the food!

274
00:18:58.080 --> 00:19:00.990
You guys saved our lives!

275
00:19:00.990 --> 00:19:02.750
So good!

276
00:19:02.750 --> 00:19:04.120
I feel alive again!

277
00:19:06.250 --> 00:19:08.380
I'm feeling great thanks to you guys!

278
00:19:08.380 --> 00:19:10.500
Hey, they're our enemies!

279
00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:11.710
Keep your voice down.

280
00:19:11.710 --> 00:19:14.380
Now just let us out of here!

281
00:19:14.380 --> 00:19:18.350
I'm glad you guys are feeling better,
but that's a little too much to ask.

282
00:19:18.350 --> 00:19:20.930
Then, could you at least relocate us?

283
00:19:21.430 --> 00:19:24.850
Hard to relax with those things around...

284
00:19:25.560 --> 00:19:27.480
There a problem down there?

285
00:19:27.850 --> 00:19:30.480
I thought the seraphim were on your side.

286
00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:33.690
Yeah, but in case they go berserk...

287
00:19:33.690 --> 00:19:36.450
It'll be fine, right, Vegapunk?

288
00:19:36.450 --> 00:19:37.660
Certainly.

289
00:19:38.030 --> 00:19:40.450
Those bubble balls

290
00:19:40.450 --> 00:19:44.710
are made of the same material
as the pacifista Mk. III's bubble shields,

291
00:19:44.710 --> 00:19:47.120
which are rated for cannon fire.

292
00:19:47.460 --> 00:19:50.920
They're infused with sea energy,

293
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:55.170
making them perfect weapons
for trapping those with powers.

294
00:19:55.170 --> 00:19:58.340
Ah, I see... I thought they were
just ordinary bubbles...

295
00:19:58.800 --> 00:20:01.300
You dare to trap me in this thing?

296
00:20:02.430 --> 00:20:04.810
There's no need to fear us.

297
00:20:04.810 --> 00:20:08.520
None of us were ordered to kill you.

298
00:20:09.020 --> 00:20:10.940
We have no interest in you!

299
00:20:11.480 --> 00:20:13.150
Y-You don't say...

300
00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:15.240
Then there's no reason to worry...

301
00:20:15.610 --> 00:20:20.490
But I really gotta thank you, S-Snake!

302
00:20:21.200 --> 00:20:24.450
You undid our petrifications!

303
00:20:24.450 --> 00:20:26.330
Did she, now?

304
00:20:26.330 --> 00:20:27.460
Peculiar...

305
00:20:27.460 --> 00:20:31.290
I never programmed S-Snake to do that...

306
00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:35.300
Hey, Hancock!

307
00:20:35.710 --> 00:20:37.300
Those guys are my friends!

308
00:20:37.300 --> 00:20:38.840
You gotta turn 'em back!

309
00:20:38.840 --> 00:20:39.510
What?

310
00:20:39.510 --> 00:20:41.850
You're the only one who can save them!

311
00:20:41.850 --> 00:20:42.800
Please!

312
00:20:45.220 --> 00:20:47.390
F-Fine!

313
00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:51.400
I will, so please stop looking at me...

314
00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:54.150
Oh, is that what happened?

315
00:20:54.150 --> 00:20:59.150
Well, even the original Hancock,
awful as she is, has a soft spot for Luffy.

316
00:20:59.150 --> 00:21:01.410
How funny!

317
00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:04.910
Her seraphim is the same way!

318
00:21:04.910 --> 00:21:07.200
Oh, Hancock!

319
00:21:07.200 --> 00:21:09.120
Hancock!

320
00:21:08.120 --> 00:21:12.790
The information transmitted through
the hereditary elements when producing clones...

321
00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:10.120
Hey!

322
00:21:10.120 --> 00:21:12.790
I'm over here, Hancock!

323
00:21:12.790 --> 00:21:14.250
Hey, over here!
is quite interesting!

324
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:17.760
I seriously owe you, Hancock!

325
00:21:17.760 --> 00:21:21.470
Owe you... Owe you... Owe you...

326
00:21:21.470 --> 00:21:22.590
What?

327
00:21:22.590 --> 00:21:24.970
Did you just say "I love you"?!

328
00:21:32.400 --> 00:21:33.560
Stella!

329
00:21:33.560 --> 00:21:36.440
The communications system
has been restored,

330
00:21:36.440 --> 00:21:39.320
but the Frontier Dome still won't open!

331
00:21:40.570 --> 00:21:42.200
It's no use!

332
00:21:43.030 --> 00:21:45.410
I protected it with a passcode.

333
00:21:45.410 --> 00:21:47.990
But my brain's not synced
with the rest of yours,

334
00:21:47.990 --> 00:21:49.750
and I'm not telling!

335
00:21:49.750 --> 00:21:51.500
Oh yeah?!

336
00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:53.790
Let's just see about that!

337
00:21:53.790 --> 00:21:56.130
Cool it, Lilith!

338
00:21:58.210 --> 00:22:01.220
I'm being protected by both
the code and the world itself.

339
00:22:01.220 --> 00:22:03.680
Boy, I'm hungry...

340
00:22:04.470 --> 00:22:05.890
Why, you little...!

341
00:22:06.260 --> 00:22:09.140
If we can't deactivate the barrier,
then there's no escape.

342
00:22:09.140 --> 00:22:12.890
Seriously? Even after
all my expert negotiating?

343
00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:14.900
I told you that didn't help.

344
00:22:21.950 --> 00:22:24.030
Four seriously injured...

345
00:22:24.030 --> 00:22:26.160
Two of Vegapunk's satellites dead...

346
00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:29.290
And the Straw Hats are...

347
00:22:29.290 --> 00:22:31.750
Penny for your thoughts, Lucci?

348
00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:34.580
Just mumbling to myself.

349
00:22:36.960 --> 00:22:41.720
We're surrounded on all sides, Stella.

350
00:22:41.720 --> 00:22:43.720
Mistress Stussy!

351
00:22:43.720 --> 00:22:47.930
There are about 100 ships of various sizes
and 30,000 soldiers out there.

352
00:22:49.220 --> 00:22:50.680
Quite the pickle.

353
00:22:50.680 --> 00:22:53.230
Welcome back, Mistress Stussy!

354
00:22:53.230 --> 00:22:55.310
How about a coffee?

355
00:22:55.310 --> 00:22:56.400
Why, thank you.

356
00:22:58.230 --> 00:22:59.860
Don't give me that look.

357
00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:03.150
So you would be Nami, the navigator?

358
00:23:03.150 --> 00:23:04.860
Yep, that's me!

359
00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.820
Tell me a bit about our route.

360
00:23:06.820 --> 00:23:09.580
The log pose hasn't recorded the signal yet,

361
00:23:09.580 --> 00:23:12.040
but we have one steady needle from Wano.

362
00:23:12.410 --> 00:23:14.330
It's pointing northeast...

363
00:23:14.330 --> 00:23:16.250
Ah, to Elbaph, then.

364
00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:18.460
– Elbaph?!
– Elbaph?!

365
00:23:18.460 --> 00:23:19.630
Are we going there?!

366
00:23:19.630 --> 00:23:20.960
Finally?!

367
00:23:20.960 --> 00:23:22.340
Seems like it.

368
00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:24.130
– Our long awaited...
– Our long awaited...

369
00:23:25.880 --> 00:23:28.470
– Isle of Giants!
– Isle of Giants!

370
00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:31.810
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph! ♪
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph! ♪

371
00:23:31.810 --> 00:23:36.440
♪ Everyone's huge, 'cause they're giants! ♪
♪ Everyone's huge, 'cause they're giants! ♪

372
00:23:31.810 --> 00:23:34.560
What's got them so excited?

373
00:23:37.730 --> 00:23:39.150
Fortunately for us,

374
00:23:39.650 --> 00:23:43.110
your ship is currently in the Labophase.

375
00:23:43.610 --> 00:23:46.610
The Marine ships are off
the shore in all directions.

376
00:23:46.610 --> 00:23:49.070
Sailing out of the port is impossible!

377
00:23:49.570 --> 00:23:51.790
We'd be heading northeast,

378
00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:54.500
which is at the island's backside.

379
00:23:54.500 --> 00:23:58.120
Luckily, your ship is next to the Vegaforce-01.

380
00:23:58.540 --> 00:24:03.590
We could use the Vegaforce-01
to fly over the Marines' blockade,

381
00:24:03.590 --> 00:24:08.090
but that robot can only fly
within the airspace over Egghead.

382
00:24:03.590 --> 00:24:11.550
Flight-Capable Airspace

383
00:24:08.090 --> 00:24:11.550
It'll plummet as soon as
it leaves that area.

384
00:24:11.550 --> 00:24:13.640
That's not far enough to escape!

385
00:24:13.640 --> 00:24:14.770
Wrong!

386
00:24:14.770 --> 00:24:19.770
When we hit that point, we'll use
the Sunny's Coup de Burst to fly farther!

387
00:24:19.770 --> 00:24:23.480
If we can make it at least a kilometer away,
no one's gonna catch us, right?

388
00:24:23.480 --> 00:24:24.860
What?!

389
00:24:24.860 --> 00:24:27.200
Your ship can fly that far?!

390
00:24:27.200 --> 00:24:29.450
She flies on cola, baby!

391
00:24:29.450 --> 00:24:30.950
On cola?!

392
00:24:31.320 --> 00:24:32.530
Mm-hm!

393
00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:42.380
Perfect! We'll run with that!

394
00:24:42.380 --> 00:24:43.090
Damn straight!

395
00:24:44.000 --> 00:24:45.130
Lilith!

396
00:24:45.130 --> 00:24:47.130
Use the Vegaforce-01 to...

397
00:24:47.130 --> 00:24:48.630
Way ahead of you!

398
00:24:48.630 --> 00:24:51.720
Move Straw Hat's ship
to the island's rear, right?

399
00:24:52.220 --> 00:24:53.600
Okay!

400
00:24:53.600 --> 00:24:57.060
But first, we have to
deactivate the Frontier Dome.

401
00:24:57.060 --> 00:24:59.560
You're not getting the code out of me!

402
00:25:07.110 --> 00:25:08.360
Let's get cracking!

403
00:25:08.360 --> 00:25:10.110
– Never underestimate Vegapunk!
– Never underestimate Vegapunk!

404
00:25:12.070 --> 00:25:14.450
Looks like we've got a plan in motion.

405
00:25:14.450 --> 00:25:18.540
I'm not so sure it'll work out
how we want it to, though...

406
00:25:20.040 --> 00:25:23.460
We won't know until we try.

407
00:25:23.460 --> 00:25:24.460
True.

408
00:25:25.000 --> 00:25:28.970
If you're headed over to
the Sunny, I'll go with you.

409
00:25:29.340 --> 00:25:30.470
Me, too!

410
00:25:30.470 --> 00:25:32.590
Let's hurry up and leave for Elbaph!

411
00:25:32.590 --> 00:25:33.930
I'll help out, too!

412
00:25:34.430 --> 00:25:36.390
Oh, thanks!

413
00:25:38.600 --> 00:25:40.270
Alright!

414
00:25:46.650 --> 00:25:50.030
The operation is a-go!

415
00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:59.120
Let's hurry and get the ship around back!

416
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:01.620
The barrier could come down at any minute!

417
00:26:01.620 --> 00:26:04.710
Right... Let's hope there
won't be any more problems.

418
00:26:04.710 --> 00:26:07.090
Don't you want it to come down?

419
00:26:07.090 --> 00:26:10.550
Sure I do, but if we're able to slip through it,

420
00:26:10.550 --> 00:26:13.890
it also means we're open
to the enemy's attacks.

421
00:26:13.890 --> 00:26:15.510
Ah, makes sense!

422
00:26:15.510 --> 00:26:19.850
This is actually my first time
leaving the island!

423
00:26:19.850 --> 00:26:21.730
C'mon, this ain't a field trip!

424
00:26:23.140 --> 00:26:24.690
Either way...

425
00:26:26.150 --> 00:26:28.400
We need more food!

426
00:26:28.400 --> 00:26:29.480
Seconded!

427
00:26:29.900 --> 00:26:32.240
We'll eat all of this in one day!

428
00:26:32.240 --> 00:26:33.700
Let's get some more pizza!

429
00:26:33.700 --> 00:26:35.700
All we need is cheese.

430
00:26:35.700 --> 00:26:38.330
If we have the ingredients,
Sanji will make us pizza.

431
00:26:40.160 --> 00:26:41.700
He's pretty handy, huh?

432
00:26:41.700 --> 00:26:43.540
A good cook and a good fighter!

433
00:26:43.540 --> 00:26:44.790
Huh?

434
00:26:44.790 --> 00:26:48.750
What's with the super good mood
all of a sudden? It's kinda creepy.

435
00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:51.920
You were so mean to Apple Gramps before.

436
00:26:56.550 --> 00:26:59.640
Yeah, I decided I'm not
gonna kill Vegapunk anymore.

437
00:27:01.930 --> 00:27:05.020
Nice. Is that why you were crying all night?

438
00:27:05.020 --> 00:27:06.900
I was not!

439
00:27:08.270 --> 00:27:10.070
Transmission from Agent Rob Lucci!

440
00:27:10.610 --> 00:27:13.400
We have info about the situation in Egghead.

441
00:27:16.660 --> 00:27:18.660
Share this with all ships!

442
00:27:18.660 --> 00:27:19.450
Yes, sir!

443
00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:28.750
Did you hear that, Borsalino?

444
00:27:29.750 --> 00:27:30.960
I did.

445
00:27:31.590 --> 00:27:35.880
He was sure talking a big game,
as if he was in control,

446
00:27:35.880 --> 00:27:39.970
but it seems they're the ones trapped inside.

447
00:27:39.970 --> 00:27:44.020
The Frontier Dome is a laser
defense system, correct?

448
00:27:44.020 --> 00:27:46.270
You are light itself.

449
00:27:46.270 --> 00:27:47.520
Can you get inside?

450
00:27:47.520 --> 00:27:50.020
In all honesty, I can...

451
00:27:50.020 --> 00:27:54.240
But a dear friend of mine
is defending Vegapunk below it.

452
00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:56.360
Simply leap over him.

453
00:27:56.360 --> 00:28:02.080
It wouldn't be cool of me to humiliate
a man so determined to stand in my way.

454
00:28:02.580 --> 00:28:05.790
Please, let me at least
stay true to my principles.

455
00:28:06.250 --> 00:28:10.250
Besides, if we attack them,

456
00:28:10.250 --> 00:28:16.550
Sentomaru will order the countless
weaponized sea beasts and the fifty pacifista...

457
00:28:16.550 --> 00:28:19.970
to sink our ships.

458
00:28:19.970 --> 00:28:23.560
The damage would be catastrophic.

459
00:28:25.180 --> 00:28:27.020
Time is of the essence, then...

460
00:28:28.140 --> 00:28:30.230
Where is the power plant?

461
00:28:34.480 --> 00:28:38.110
Rob Lucci is a capable man.

462
00:28:38.110 --> 00:28:43.660
He sent us all the necessary information.

463
00:28:53.500 --> 00:28:59.220
– Prepare for battle!
– Prepare for battle!

464
00:28:59.590 --> 00:29:03.180
All Six Powers users, make for land
as soon as the battle commences!

465
00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:06.890
Free the captured Cipher Pol agents!

466
00:29:07.480 --> 00:29:10.770
Artillery fire won't work on the pacifista!

467
00:29:10.770 --> 00:29:14.230
Aim for the weaponized sea beasts!

468
00:29:24.370 --> 00:29:26.620
This is super fun!

469
00:29:26.620 --> 00:29:28.330
It's ground from a sky island!

470
00:29:31.170 --> 00:29:34.170
I get it, man, but we gotta get serious!

471
00:29:35.840 --> 00:29:36.550
Look!

472
00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:38.210
There's the Sunny!

473
00:29:47.890 --> 00:29:49.600
Well then...

474
00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:51.980
Sacred Yata Mirror.

475
00:30:11.080 --> 00:30:13.420
You're finally here, Unc!

476
00:30:13.420 --> 00:30:15.420
Pacifista!

477
00:30:31.140 --> 00:30:34.600
Here I come, Sentomaru!

478
00:30:37.150 --> 00:30:39.110
Bring it, Unc!

479
00:30:40.030 --> 00:30:42.740
My defense...

480
00:30:43.700 --> 00:30:46.820
is the greatest in the world!

481
00:30:56.830 --> 00:30:58.340
Huh...?

482
00:30:58.340 --> 00:30:59.550
What's that?!

483
00:30:59.920 --> 00:31:01.760
Light from below?!

484
00:31:05.010 --> 00:31:06.720
There's someone here!

485
00:31:07.550 --> 00:31:09.010
Someone strong!
